import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="darkgrid")
    sns.histplot(data=data, x="open", kde=True, color="blue")
    plt.axvline(data['open'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean = {data['open'].mean():,.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['open'].median(), color='g', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median = {data['open'].median():,.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.xlabel('Opening Price')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of opening prices?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='close', data=data, color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the trend of closing prices over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Closing Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='high', y='low')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between the highest and lowest prices?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    sns.distplot(data['volume'], kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['volume'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Mean Volume = {:.2f}'.format(data['volume'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(data['volume'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Median Volume = {:.2f}'.format(data['volume'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Volume')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of volumes?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
